    "Remember: 'buongiorno' for morning, 'buonasera' from late afternoon, 'buonanotte' only at bedtime.",
    "Formal vs. informal is one of the most important distinctions in Italian. When in doubt, use the formal form — Italians appreciate politeness.",
    "You now know the essential survival phrases: greetings, politeness, asking how someone is, and what to say when you're lost. These will carry you through your first Italian conversations!"
